content: NC.lab-member-Tianyu Qiu This picture was taken at Presidential Palace, NanJing, China by one of my best friends when I came to NanJing for my postgraduate reexamination. (PS: So silly...lol) 邱天宇 Tian-yu Qiu M. Sc. Student Department of Computer Science & Technology, Nanjing University, China Supervisor     Resume     Research Interest     Publication     Correspondence Supervisor: professor Furao Shen Resume: Currently I am a first year graduate student of Department of Computer Science and Technology in Nanjing University and a member of RINC Lab, led by professor Furao Shen. I received my B.Eng. degree in Electrical Engineering and Automation in June 2013 from East China JiaoTong University. Fortunately, I was admitted to study for a M.Sc. degree in Nanjing University in the same year. Research Interest: Currently I am interested in statistical approaches to AI, include: Statistical Learning, Artificial Neural Networks.
